You haven&#39;t included enough information to be sure, but it&#39;s fairly likely
that you have a classpath problem.  These can be infuriatingly subtle at
times.  When I have encountered this kind of problem, it occurred because
a class in a jar loaded by the system classloader was trying to load a
class that I had just written.  My source directory wasn&#39;t on the system
classloader&#39;s classpath, so it couldn&#39;t find it.

